    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is designed as a high-fidelity, interactive simulation of the Perplexity AI interface. This structure was chosen because it provides the most intuitive and engaging way to understand the platform's navigation and features, aligning with the goal of 'learning by doing'. The layout is a persistent two-panel design: a fixed left sidebar for primary navigation (mirroring the real app) and a dynamic main content area that updates based on user interaction. This non-linear structure allows users to freely explore features like 'Home', 'Discover', 'Spaces', and 'About Perplexity', in any order. User flow is driven by clicks, which trigger view changes and modals containing explanatory text derived directly from the source analysis, effectively making the application itself an interactive report. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: The application translates the source report's analysis into interactive components rather than static text or charts. 
        - Report Info: Core Navigation (Sidebar) -> Goal: Demonstrate app structure -> Viz/Method: Interactive HTML/Tailwind sidebar -> Interaction: Clicks on 'Home', 'Discover', 'Spaces', 'About Perplexity' dynamically change the main content view, simulating navigation.
        - Report Info: Search Bar Functions (Focus, Attach, Pro Toggle, Content Type, Microphone, Send) -> Goal: Explain precise search query controls -> Viz/Method: Clickable HTML buttons/icons embedded directly within the search bar's input field, matching the screenshot's layout. -> Interaction: Clicking these elements opens a modal with a detailed explanation of their function.
        - Report Info: UX Principle (Visibility of System Status) -> Goal: Demonstrate responsive AI feedback -> Viz/Method: A CSS/JS "thinking" animation with text -> Interaction: Triggered upon clicking the search button to simulate the AI's process.
        - Report Info: Content Discovery (Quick Access Buttons) -> Goal: Illustrate guided entry points -> Viz/Method: Interactive HTML buttons below the search bar -> Interaction: Clicking a button pre-fills the search bar and runs a simulated query, showing an immediate use case.
        - Report Info: Perplexity Overview/Key Features -> Goal: Provide high-level understanding of the product -> Viz/Method: Dedicated 'About Perplexity' page with summarized text and feature list from the analysis -> Interaction: Navigation via sidebar link.
        - Justification: This interactive simulation approach is superior to static charts or text for teaching a user interface, as it provides direct, hands-on experience with the navigation and features. The precise replication of the search bar layout enhances fidelity. The addition of an 'About' page enhances understanding by providing core contextual information about the product itself. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
